}{}$ \frac{M}{M+U+offset} $\end{document}MM+U+offset . Here, M is the methylated intensity and U is the unmethylated intensity; the offset is a constant added to regularize the βvalue where both methylated and unmethylated intensities are low. The distribution of β values is bimodal, with peaks corresponding to methylated and unmethylated states, but the distribution of Infinium II probes differs from that of Infinium I, being more compressed towards 0.5 (Pidsley et al., 2013) and hence having a smaller dynamic range (Teschendorff et al., 2013; Dedeurwaerder et al., 2014).
